.TH "pinctrl_gpio_request" 9 "pinctrl_gpio_request" "May 2021" "Kernel Hacker's Manual" LINUX
.SH NAME
pinctrl_gpio_request \- request a single pin to be used as GPIO
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B "int" pinctrl_gpio_request
.BI "(unsigned gpio "  ");"
.SH ARGUMENTS
.IP "gpio" 12
the GPIO pin number from the GPIO subsystem number space
.SH "DESCRIPTION"
This function should *ONLY* be used from gpiolib-based GPIO drivers,
as part of their \fBgpio_request\fP semantics, platforms and individual drivers
shall *NOT* request GPIO pins to be muxed in.
